    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Text Spacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "In this chapter you will learn about the following properties:"
    },
    {
      "type": "other",
      "text": "text-indent\nletter-spacing\nline-height\n  word-spacing\n  white-space"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Text Indentation"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The text-indent property is used to specify the indentation of the first line of a text:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "p {  text-indent: 50px;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Letter Spacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The letter-spacing property is used to specify the space between the characters in a text."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following example demonstrates how to increase or decrease the space between characters:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "h1 {  letter-spacing: 5px;}h2 {  letter-spacing: -2px;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Line Height"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The line-height property is used to specify the space between lines:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "p.small {  line-height: 0.8;}p.big {  \nline-height: 1.8;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Word Spacing"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The word-spacing property is used to specify the space between \nthe words in a text."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The following example demonstrates how to increase or decrease the space between \nwords:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "p.one {  word-spacing: 10px;}p.two {  word-spacing: -2px;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "White Space"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The white-space property specifies how white-space inside an element is handled."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This example demonstrates how to disable text wrapping inside an element:"
    },
    {
      "type": "example",
      "description": "",
      "codes": [
        {
          "language": "unknown",
          "code": "p {  white-space: nowrap;}"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "The CSS Text Spacing Properties"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "data": [
        [
          "Property",
          "Description"
        ],
        [
          "letter-spacing",
          "Specifies the space between characters in a text"
        ],
        [
          "line-height",
          "Specifies the line height"
        ],
        [
          "text-indent",
          "Specifies the indentation of the first line in a text-block"
        ],
        [
          "white-space",
          "Specifies how to handle white-space inside an element"
        ],
        [
          "word-spacing",
          "Specifies the space between words in a text"
        ]
      ]
    },
